Package: lazyplyr
Type: Package
Title: a most lazy dplyr implementation for remote data frames
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2021-03-24
Authors@R:
    c(person("Mark", "Klik", email = "markklik@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")))
Description: Provides a toolset for interfacing with out of memory datasets using the dplyr interface. All dplyr verbs are computed in the most laziest possible manner to minimize RAM usage and data transfer to offline systems.
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0)
License: MPL-2.0 | file LICENSE
Imports:
    crayon,
    dplyr,
    pillar,
    rlang,
    tidyselect
Suggests:
    knitr,
    lintr,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: 
    knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
URL: https://fstpackage.github.io/lazyplyr
BugReports: https://github.com/fstpackage/lazyplyr/issues
